.TH "write_ofld_wr" 9 "write_ofld_wr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
write_ofld_wr \- write an offload work request
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" write_ofld_wr
.BI "(struct adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "struct sge_txq *q "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pidx "  ","
.BI "unsigned int gen "  ","
.BI "unsigned int ndesc "  ","
.BI "const dma_addr_t *addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
the adapter
.IP "skb" 12
the packet to send
.IP "q" 12
the Tx queue
.IP "pidx" 12
index of the first Tx descriptor to write
.IP "gen" 12
the generation value to use
.IP "ndesc" 12
number of descriptors the packet will occupy
.IP "addr" 12
the address

Write an offload work request to send the supplied packet.  The packet
data already carry the work request with most fields populated.
